New Records: David Warner scored 163 runs, his highest in an ODI match.
Mohammad Afridi took 5 wickets for 54 runs, his best bowling performance in ODIs.
Key Match Events: Pakistan collapsed from 292-8 to 305-9, losing by 62 runs.
Australia's batting performance set the tone with 367-9 in 50 overs.
Key dismissals included Hasan Ali and Usama Mir, with Labuschagne and Stoinis contributing to crucial catches.
Pre-Game Insights: Pat Cummins emphasized Australia's aggressive approach and the importance of their Powerplay performance.
Babar Azam acknowledged Pakistan's inconsistencies and the impact of dropped catches.
Post-Match Reflections: Cummins praised the team's resilience and the openers' performance.
Azam expressed frustration with the team's inability to maintain consistency and capitalize on partnerships.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was significant as it moved Australia level on points with Pakistan and South Africa in the World Cup.
The Proteas have a break before facing the Netherlands, while Pakistan prepares to face Bangladesh.
